# Envoir self-host — example environment file.
#
#   cp deploy/.env.example deploy/.env
#   # edit deploy/.env
#   docker compose -f deploy/docker-compose.yml --env-file deploy/.env up --build -d
#
# Every variable below is read by deploy/docker-compose.yml, which in turn hands the GATEWAY_*
# ones straight to the real `envoir-gateway` binary as environment variables (see
# gateway/src/main.rs / gateway/src/personal.rs — the binary actually reads ~30 GATEWAY_* vars in
# total; the 5 below are the ones this compose stack wires up today, nothing here is invented).
# `envoir-node` has its own real ENVOIR_* environment-variable surface (~25 vars, node/src/config.rs)
# — see the "envoir-node" section near the bottom of this file, and deploy/README.md.

# --- gateway/src/main.rs: GATEWAY_DOMAIN ---
# The domain this gateway is the MX for. Must match your real public DNS MX record if you intend
# to receive real internet mail; the gateway does not verify this against anything itself.
GATEWAY_DOMAIN=localhost

# --- docker-compose.yml: host-side published port for the gateway's inbound MX listener ---
# The container always listens on 2525 internally (see Dockerfile.gateway EXPOSE); this is only
# the host-side port docker-compose publishes it on. Real inbound internet mail arrives on 25,
# which you'd need to forward to this port at your firewall/router (2525 is used internally so
# the container does not need root / cap_net_bind_service for a privileged port).
GATEWAY_PORT=2525

# --- gateway/src/main.rs: GATEWAY_GW_SELECTOR ---
# The DKIM-delegated-selector name this gateway signs outbound legacy mail with (spec §7.3,
# RFC 8463 ed25519-sha256). Purely a label; must match whatever selector you publish in DNS
# alongside the delegated signing key once that publishing step is wired up (see README §DNS).
GATEWAY_GW_SELECTOR=gw1

# --- gateway/src/main.rs: GATEWAY_DNS_SERVER ---
# ip:port of the DNS resolver the gateway's hand-rolled UDP client (gateway/src/dns.rs) queries
# for outbound MX / MTA-STS TXT lookups. It does NOT read /etc/resolv.conf. Point this at a
# resolver you trust (a local unbound/knot-resolver, your registrar's, or a public one).
GATEWAY_DNS_SERVER=1.1.1.1:53

# --- gateway/src/main.rs: GATEWAY_TLS_CERT / GATEWAY_TLS_KEY (paths INSIDE the container) ---
# Leave BOTH LINES COMMENTED OUT (not just empty!) to run a plaintext dev listener (no STARTTLS
# offered — fine for local testing, NOT fine for anything internet-facing). This matters:
# `envoir-gateway` checks whether the env var is *set at all*, so `GATEWAY_TLS_CERT=` (set but
# empty) is treated as "configured" and it then fails trying to open a PEM file at path ""
# (verified: the gateway container crash-loops with "No such file or directory" if these are
# merely blank rather than absent/commented). To enable STARTTLS on the inbound MX leg, drop your
# PEM cert chain + private key into ./deploy/certs/ (mounted read-only at /certs) and UNCOMMENT
# both lines below with real in-container paths, e.g.:
#   GATEWAY_TLS_CERT=/certs/fullchain.pem
#   GATEWAY_TLS_KEY=/certs/privkey.pem

# --- NOT overridable here: GATEWAY_LISTEN ---
# docker-compose.yml hardcodes GATEWAY_LISTEN=0.0.0.0:2525 (not exposed as a .env variable) so the
# GATEWAY_PORT publish above actually reaches the process. The binary's own default,
# 127.0.0.1:2525, only accepts loopback connections *inside the container's network namespace* —
# verified to NOT be reachable through a published Docker port. Don't change this back to a
# 127.0.0.1 address unless you know you don't need the published port.

# --- envoir-node (node/src/config.rs) ---
# The node reads its own real ENVOIR_* environment variables — every one has a sane default, so
# `docker compose up` works with none of these set. docker-compose.yml sets ENVOIR_DATA_DIR=/data
# (the node-data volume) directly; the rest are documented here for when you need to override one
# (e.g. add `- ENVOIR_JMAP=1` etc. to the node service's `environment:` block).
#
#   ENVOIR_DATA_DIR          data dir for keystore.json + journal.json      (default ./envoir-data)
#   ENVOIR_NODE_BIND         mesh transport bind (host:port)                (default 0.0.0.0:4600)
#   ENVOIR_PASSPHRASE        keystore passphrase; unset = plaintext-for-dev (default unset)
#   ENVOIR_NAMES             comma-separated claimed names (§3.2)           (default empty)
#   ENVOIR_KT_ANCHORS        comma-separated KT log anchor URL(s) (§3.5.2)  (default a placeholder)
#   ENVOIR_KEYPKGS_LOC       KeyPackage bundle locator (§5.3)               (default /mesh/kp/self)
#   ENVOIR_TICK_SECS         daemon retry/poll/deadline tick interval      (default 15)
#   ENVOIR_FORCE_INIT        =1: `init` overwrites an existing keystore     (default unset)
#   ENVOIR_SUPERVISED        =1: `run` treats stdin EOF as shutdown         (default unset — off)
#   ENVOIR_SEND_API          =1: enable the Envoir Send HTTP API (§13.5.1)  (default unset — off)
#   ENVOIR_SEND_API_BIND     Envoir Send HTTP bind                          (default 0.0.0.0:4610)
#   ENVOIR_SEND_ADMIN_TOKEN  admin bearer token; unset = key mgmt disabled  (default unset)
#   ENVOIR_JMAP              =1: enable the node-native JMAP listener (§8.1) (default unset — off)
#   ENVOIR_JMAP_BIND         JMAP bind; off-localhost requires a TLS front  (default 127.0.0.1:4700)
#   ENVOIR_JMAP_APP_PASSWORDS  comma-separated user:secret app-passwords    (default empty — fail-closed)
#   ENVOIR_JMAP_ACCOUNT      JMAP accountId; unset = derived from name/key  (default unset)
#   ENVOIR_JMAP_BASE_URL     externally-reachable JMAP Session base URL     (default derived from bind)
#   ENVOIR_PUB_SERVE         =1: serve the DMTAP-PUB gateway (§22.5/§22.6)  (default unset — off)
#   ENVOIR_PUB_BIND          DMTAP-PUB bind                                 (default 0.0.0.0:4680)
#   ENVOIR_SYNC_SERVE        =1: serve the Sync reconciliation surface      (default unset — off)
#   ENVOIR_SYNC_BIND         Sync bind                                      (default 127.0.0.1:4690)
#   ENVOIR_SYNC_NAMESPACES   comma-separated sync namespaces                (default empty — "" only)
#
# See deploy/README.md and node/src/config.rs's own doc comment for the full rationale behind
# each default.
